      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Co-Production</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dan Fields letter on David Mermelstein's June 11 article on his Los Angeles revival of Arthur Miller's Man Who Had All the Luck; note show was co-production of Antaeus Company and his New York-based company, Finesilver Shows (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In David Mermelstein's article about my Los Angeles revival of Arthur Miller's ''Man Who Had All the Luck'' [''Reviving a Forgotten Miller Play,'' June 11], the spotlight was rightly put on the Antaeus Company, a Los Angeles theater company of classically trained actors. However, this very successful show was in fact a co-production of Antaeus and my New York-based company, Finesilver Shows. Perhaps more bicoastal collaborations will fuel support for straight plays in both of these thriving theater cities.</p>
        <p>DAN FIELDS  Manhattan</p>
      </block>
